[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by coldness, as of manner, influence,
etc.; chilling; frigid; cold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Icy</qex> was the deportment with which Philip received these
demonstrations of affection.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

